, \"from\": 311, \"to\": 324}, {\"ngram\": \"then the small matter\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 385}, {\"ngram\": \"just about the most iconic structure\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 425}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 439}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect, cloudless sky\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yesterday morning, with the triathlon kiboshed by bacterial gremlins in the Seine, seemed a good opportunity to trundle down to theEiffel Tower's beach volleyball court and check out the scene that is making all the early running in the race to emerge as the defining image of these Games.\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 769, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 556, \"end\": 561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4528900242618715e-28, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the triathlon\", \"from\": 504, \"to\": 517}, {\"ngram\": \"bacterial gremlins\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 548}, {\"ngram\": \"a good opportunity\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 588}, {\"ngram\": \"theEiffel Tower's beach volleyball court\", \"from\": 608, \"to\": 648}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 672}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 721}, {\"ngram\": \"the defining image\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 753}, {\"ngram\": \"these Games\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 768}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And not to get all wish-you-were-here about it, but even having already seen all the television montages, the drone swoops and the Instagram snaps, nothing quite prepared you for the real thing.\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 965, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 902, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1930148180671104e-37, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all wish\", \"from\": 786, \"to\": 794}, {\"ngram\": \"all the television montages\", \"from\": 848, \"to\": 875}, {\"ngram\": \"the drone swoops\", \"from\": 877, \"to\": 893}, {\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 919, \"to\": 926}, {\"ngram\": \"the real thing\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 964}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is utterly magnificent.\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 992, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is whatParisintended when it gambled on the weather for Friday night's opening ceremony and lost: a Games woven into a city that could shine all on its own, little cash wasted on flash, purpose-built venues, when temporary facilities set against postcard backdrops could do the job twice as well.\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1295, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the weather\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday night's opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1086}, {\"ngram\": \"a city\", \"from\": 1116, \"to\": 1122}, {\"ngram\": \"its own, little cash\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1167}, {\"ngram\": \"flash, purpose-built venues\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1205}, {\"ngram\": \"temporary facilities\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1232}, {\"ngram\": \"postcard backdrops\", \"from\": 1245, \"to\": 1263}, {\"ngram\": \"the job\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1280}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other hosts have done similar things before - Rio had Copacabana, the most famous actual beach on the planet, to host its volleyball andLondontook the same sport to Horse Guards Parade - but never on this scale.\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1508, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1462, \"end\": 1481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Horse_Guards_Parade\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Horse Guards Parade\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Horse_Guards_Parade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Horse_Guards_Parade\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other hosts\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"similar things\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1333}, {\"ngram\": \"Rio\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1346}, {\"ngram\": \"Copacabana\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1361}, {\"ngram\": \"the most famous actual beach\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1391}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1405}, {\"ngram\": \"its volleyball andLondontook\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1443}, {\"ngram\": \"the same sport\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1458}, {\"ngram\": \"this scale\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1507}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Paris, there is hardly a landmark of note that has not been repurposed or transformed.\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1513, \"end\": 1518, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.946598209494589e-32, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a landmark\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1546}, {\"ngram\": \"note\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1554}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The heart of the Metro map, with famous sights-turned-Olympic venues highlighted in light purple, looks like a spilt packet of Parma Violets.\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1727, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parma_Violets\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Parma Violets\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parma_Violets\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parma_Violets\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The heart\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1609}, {\"ngram\": \"the Metro map\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1626}, {\"ngram\": \"famous sights-turned-Olympic venues\", \"from\": 1633, \"to\": 1668}, {\"ngram\": \"light purple\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"a spilt packet\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Public transport is optional - and on a scorching day like this, as I will later discover, probably advisable, too - but a decent number of these central venues are close enough to hop between on foot.\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1944, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Public transport\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1759}, {\"ngram\": \"a scorching day\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1796}, {\"ngram\": \"a decent number\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1879}, {\"ngram\": \"these central venues\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1903}, {\"ngram\": \"foot\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 1943}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the base of the Eiffel Tower, where deckchairs and soft Ibiza mixes add to the beach club vibe, a stroll along the Seine takes you to the Grand Palais, basically Ally Pally on steroids.\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 2135, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2065, \"end\": 2070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4528900242618715e-28, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the base\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1958}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"deckchairs\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 1996}, {\"ngram\": \"soft Ibiza mixes\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2017}, {\"ngram\": \"the beach club vibe\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2044}, {\"ngram\": \"a stroll\", \"from\": 2046, \"to\": 2054}, {\"ngram\": \"the Grand Palais\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2100}, {\"ngram\": \"steroids\", \"from\": 2126, \"to\": 2134}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Axelle Saint-Cirel's epic rendition of 'La Marseillaise' from atop its roof was one of a grey opening ceremony's redeeming moments, but since the Games officially began it has been home to fencing, historically France's most successful Olympic sport.\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2387, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2348, \"end\": 2354, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999998150660929, \"rank\": 1.8434596771225903e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Axelle Saint-Cirel's epic rendition\", \"from\": 2137, \"to\": 2172}, {\"ngram\": \"La Marseillaise\", \"from\": 2177, \"to\": 2192}, {\"ngram\": \"its roof\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2212}, {\"ngram\": \"a grey opening ceremony's redeeming moments\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2267}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2288}, {\"ngram\": \"fencing\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2333}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fresh from hosting a gripping all-French final of the women's sabre on Tuesday night, the mood is again riotous as the home female \\u00e9p\\u00e9e team take to the piste for their opener against South Korea.\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2573, \"end\": 2584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999999998844942, \"rank\": 1.0256557076041844e-10, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a gripping all-French final\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2435}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's sabre\", \"from\": 2439, \"to\": 2456}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesday night\", \"from\": 2460, \"to\": 2473}, {\"ngram\": \"the mood\", \"from\": 2475, \"to\": 2483}, {\"ngram\": \"the home female \\u00e9p\\u00e9e team\", \"from\": 2504, \"to\": 2529}, {\"ngram\": \"the piste\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2547}, {\"ngram\": \"their opener\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2564}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are four matches going on at once, but everyone is watching the same one - the bloke in the Antoine Griezmann shirt, the woman in the silly tricolour cockerel hat - as the choruses of \\\"Allez Les Bleus\\\" attest.\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2684, \"end\": 2701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antoine_Griezmann\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Antoine Griezmann\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antoine_Griezmann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Antoine_Griezmann\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"four matches\", \"from\": 2596, \"to\": 2608}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 2631, \"to\": 2639}, {\"ngram\": \"the bloke\", \"from\": 2667, \"to\": 2676}, {\"ngram\": \"the woman\", \"from\": 2709, \"to\": 2718}, {\"ngram\": \"the silly tricolour cockerel hat\", \"from\": 2722, \"to\": 2754}, {\"ngram\": \"the choruses\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2772}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"Allez Les Bleus\\\" attest\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2800}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They win, though I am no longer there to see the victorious moment, already back on the Champs \\u00c9lys\\u00e9es for the next leg of this whistle-stop tour.\", \"from\": 2803, \"to\": 2949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2891, \"end\": 2905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"score\": 0.9999999957353793, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Champs \\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the victorious moment\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2869}, {\"ngram\": \"the next leg\", \"from\": 2910, \"to\": 2922}, {\"ngram\": \"this whistle-stop tour\", \"from\": 2926, \"to\": 2948}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But I know because of the distant cheer, the kind that makes you regret leaving a football match early when you are halfway back to the Tube.\", \"from\": 2950, \"to\": 3091, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the distant cheer\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 2989}, {\"ngram\": \"the kind\", \"from\": 2991, \"to\": 2999}, {\"ngram\": \"a football match\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3046}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tube\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3090}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Except this is forfencing.\", \"from\": 3092, \"to\": 3118, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"House prices increased by 2.5% in November despite Budget concerns London jobs crisis: Reeves hit hiring and is driving posts abroad, says Currys boss Jobs crisis for London as unemployment rate doubles in less than two years Discover a hidden island paradise in the Indian Ocean A glance right, along the sightline of Pont Alexandre III, reveals the golden dome of Les Invalides, home to Napoleon's tomb and, for these few days, Olympic archery.\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3120, \"end\": 3125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\", \"score\": 0.9999989185349868, \"rank\": 9.844513906719325e-07, \"text\": \"House\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_music\"}, {\"begin\": 3188, \"end\": 3194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999317879, \"rank\": 6.800471706938136e-11, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 3260, \"end\": 3266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Currys\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Currys\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Currys\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Currys\"}, {\"begin\": 3289, \"end\": 3295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999317879, \"rank\": 6.800471706938136e-11, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/res